bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Roger Bagnall is a papyrologist and a historian of the Hellenistic, Roman, and late antique eastern Mediterranean specializing in Graeco-Roman Egypt.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged into 17 series:

list.item: Series V: Egypt in Late Antiquity and Kellis Account Book
Series VIII: Lectures and Unpublished Work
Series IX: Ancient History Courses at Columbia
Series XII: NEH Summer Seminars & Written and Unwritten Conference
Series XVI: Commission on the Future of Libraries

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: This collection is located off-site. You will need to request this material at least twenty-four (24) hours in advance to use the collection in the Rare Book and Manuscript Library reading room.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Identification of specific item; Date (if known); Roger Bagnall Papers; Box and Folder; Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Columbia University Library

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Papers Processed by Professor Bagnall and a student assistant

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Single photocopies may be made for research purposes. Permission to publish material from the collection must be requested from the Curator of Manuscripts/University Archivist, Rare Book and Manuscript Library (RBML). The RBML approves permission to publish that which it physically owns; the responsibility to secure copyright permission rests with the patron.
